Date: Tue 28 Sep 2004 9:46 PM
From: Dr Roy Bengis <RoyB@nda.agric.za>

Yes, certain environmental, climatic, or population factors appear to be
ideal for anthrax in southern Africa this year.
To date, Kruger has been spared, and we have not detected any cases in
spite of heightened surveillance. The wet season is due to kick in within
about the next 6 weeks, and should result in a major reduction or cessation
of new cases in the currently affected areas of Zimbabwe, Botswana, and
Namibia.
--
Dr. Roy Bengis
Kruger National Park,
Skakuza, South Africa
<RoyB@nda.agric.za>
